## 5. Your Rights

You have the right to:

1. **Know** that you are interacting with an AI system — this policy and in-product labels are how we inform you.
2. **Refuse** — where the AI-powered feature is optional, you can choose not to use it. Core site functions are always available without AI.
3. **Request human review** of any AI-produced output that affects you — contact [{{config.contactEmail}}](mailto:{{config.contactEmail}}) with the specific interaction and we will review within 14 days.
4. **Contest** an AI decision that affects you — the same email address handles contestation requests.
{{#if hasHighRisk}}
5. **Object** to high-risk AI decision-making about you — for the high-risk systems listed above, we maintain human oversight under EU AI Act Article 14 and will not rely on automated output alone for decisions affecting your rights.
{{/if}}

---

## 6. AI-Generated Content Labels

Where our site displays content that was generated by an AI system (as opposed to written or produced by {{config.ownerName}} or another named human author), the content carries a visible `AI-generated` label or equivalent disclosure. Synthetic media (deepfake text, image, audio, or video) is never used to impersonate a real person.

---

## 7. Incidents

If an AI system we use produces output that causes harm, discriminates against users, or otherwise malfunctions in a way that affects your rights, that incident is handled under our [Incident Response Plan](./incident-response-plan.md) and — for high-risk systems placed on the EU market — reported to the relevant market surveillance authority without undue delay under EU AI Act Article 73.

---

## 8. Changes to This Policy

This policy is regenerated on every scan of our codebase. Material changes (a new AI provider, a new data category sent, a tier change) appear in the inventory table above. The signed commit history of the repository hosting {{config.siteName}} is the source of truth for when each change took effect.

